<paragraph blockId="15.[151,734,434,460]" box="[151,734,434,460]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,734,434,460]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,734,434,460]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Family “ 
<taxonomicName box="[260,420,434,460]" class="Trilobita" family="Laudoniidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Redlichiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Laudoniidae</taxonomicName>
” 
<bibRefCitation author="Palmer" box="[441,734,434,460]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Palmer, A. R. &amp; Repina, L. N. (1993) Through a glass darkly: Taxonomy, phylogeny, and biostratigraphy of the Olenellina. University of Kansas Paleontological Contributions, New Series, 3, 1 - 35." type="journal article" year="1993">
Palmer &amp; Repina, 
<number box="[675,734,434,460]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1993.0">1993</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,505,1034]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
The subfamily Laudoniinae 
<bibRefCitation author="Palmer" box="[468,733,505,530]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Palmer, A. R. &amp; Repina, L. N. (1993) Through a glass darkly: Taxonomy, phylogeny, and biostratigraphy of the Olenellina. University of Kansas Paleontological Contributions, New Series, 3, 1 - 35." type="journal article" year="1993">
Palmer &amp; Repina, 
<number box="[677,733,505,529]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1993.0">1993</number>
</bibRefCitation>
was originally established to include the genera 
<emphasis box="[1281,1388,505,529]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Laudonia</emphasis>
and (tentatively) 
<taxonomicName authority="Peach, 1894" authorityName="Peach" authorityYear="1894" box="[296,585,541,566]" class="Trilobita" family="Biceratopsidae" genus="Olenelloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Redlichiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[296,437,541,565]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Olenelloides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Peach" box="[446,585,541,566]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Peach, B. N. (1894) Additions to the fauna of the Olenellus - Zone of the Northwest Highlands. Quarterly Journal of the Geological Society of London, 50, 661 - 676. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1144 / gsl. jgs. 1894.050.01 - 04.44" type="journal article" year="1894">
Peach, 
<number box="[529,585,542,566]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1894.0">1894</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Palmer" box="[601,875,541,566]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Palmer, A. R. &amp; Repina, L. N. (1993) Through a glass darkly: Taxonomy, phylogeny, and biostratigraphy of the Olenellina. University of Kansas Paleontological Contributions, New Series, 3, 1 - 35." type="journal article" year="1993">
Palmer &amp; Repina, 
<number box="[816,875,542,566]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1993.0">1993</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; although if 
<taxonomicName box="[1021,1162,541,565]" class="Trilobita" family="Biceratopsidae" genus="Olenelloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Redlichiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1021,1162,541,565]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Olenelloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was placed in the same subfamily as 
<emphasis box="[300,408,577,601]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Laudonia</emphasis>
, then Olenelloidinae 
<bibRefCitation author="Hupe" box="[648,779,577,602]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Hupe, P. (1953) Classe des Trilobites. In: Piveteau, J. (Ed.), Traite de Paleontologie. Tome III. Les formes ultimes d'Invertebres: Morphologie et evolution. Onychophores, Arthropodes, Echinodermes, Stomocordes. Masson, Paris, pp. 44 - 246." type="book chapter" year="1953">
Hupé, 
<number box="[723,779,577,602]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1953.0">1953</number>
</bibRefCitation>
would have priority over Laudoniinae). 
<bibRefCitation author="Lieberman" box="[1233,1436,577,602]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Lieberman, B. S. (1998) Cladistic analysis of the Early Cambrian olenelloid trilobites. Journal of Paleontology, 72, 59 - 78." type="journal article" year="1998">
Lieberman (
<number box="[1370,1428,577,601]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1998.0">1998</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
subsequently reassigned some material of 
<emphasis box="[648,756,613,637]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Laudonia</emphasis>
to a new genus 
<taxonomicName box="[961,1166,613,637]" class="Trilobita" family="Biceratopsidae" genus="Lochmanolenellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Redlichiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[961,1166,613,637]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Lochmanolenellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The cladistic analysis presented by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lieberman" box="[303,508,649,674]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Lieberman, B. S. (1998) Cladistic analysis of the Early Cambrian olenelloid trilobites. Journal of Paleontology, 72, 59 - 78." type="journal article" year="1998">
Lieberman (
<number box="[442,500,650,674]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1998.0">1998</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
found that both 
<taxonomicName box="[700,905,649,673]" class="Trilobita" family="Biceratopsidae" genus="Lochmanolenellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Redlichiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[700,905,649,673]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Lochmanolenellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[963,1104,649,673]" class="Trilobita" family="Biceratopsidae" genus="Olenelloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Redlichiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[963,1104,649,673]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Olenelloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shared more recent common ancestry with 
<taxonomicName box="[313,411,685,709]" class="Trilobita" family="Olenellidae" genus="Bristolia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Redlichiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[313,411,685,709]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Bristolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Harrington, 1956" authorityName="Harrington" authorityYear="1956" box="[428,774,685,710]" class="Trilobita" family="Holmiidae" genus="Fremontella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Redlichiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[428,566,685,709]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fremontella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Harrington" box="[575,774,685,710]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Harrington, H. J. (1956) Olenellidae with advanced cephalic spines. Journal of Paleontology, 30, 56 - 61." type="journal article" year="1956">
Harrington, 
<number box="[715,774,685,710]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1956.0">1956</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[787,957,685,709]" class="Trilobita" family="Olenellidae" genus="Nephrolenellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Redlichiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[787,957,685,709]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Nephrolenellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Palmer and Repina, 1993" authorityName="Palmer and Repina" authorityYear="1993" box="[974,1432,685,710]" class="Trilobita" family="Olenellidae" genus="Bolbolenellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Redlichiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[974,1128,685,709]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Bolbolenellus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Palmer" box="[1138,1432,685,710]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Palmer, A. R. &amp; Repina, L. N. (1993) Through a glass darkly: Taxonomy, phylogeny, and biostratigraphy of the Olenellina. University of Kansas Paleontological Contributions, New Series, 3, 1 - 35." type="journal article" year="1993">
Palmer and Repina, 
<number box="[1373,1432,686,710]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1993.0">1993</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[151,263,721,745]" class="Trilobita" family="Holmiidae" genus="Peachella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Redlichiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,263,721,745]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Peachella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[325,446,722,745]" class="Trilobita" family="Holmiidae" genus="Biceratops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Redlichiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[325,446,722,745]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Biceratops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than with 
<emphasis box="[566,785,721,745]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Laudonia 
<taxonomicName box="[681,785,721,745]" class="Trilobita" family="Biceratopsidae" genus="Lochmanolenellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Redlichiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bispinata">bispinata</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, so 
<taxonomicName box="[832,1038,721,745]" class="Trilobita" family="Biceratopsidae" genus="Lochmanolenellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Redlichiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[832,1038,721,745]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Lochmanolenellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1093,1235,721,745]" class="Trilobita" family="Biceratopsidae" genus="Olenelloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Redlichiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1093,1235,721,745]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Olenelloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were accordingly assigned to the 
<taxonomicName authority="Pack &amp; Gayle, 1971" authorityName="Pack &amp; Gayle" authorityYear="1971" box="[323,724,757,782]" class="Trilobita" family="Biceratopsidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Redlichiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Biceratopsidae 
<bibRefCitation author="Pack" box="[495,724,757,782]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Pack, P. D. &amp; Gayle, H. B. (1971) A new olenellid trilobite, Biceratops nevadensis, from the Lower Cambrian near Las Vegas, Nevada. Journal of Paleontology, 45, 893 - 898." type="journal article" year="1971">
Pack &amp; Gayle, 
<number box="[665,724,758,782]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1971.0">1971</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis box="[734,952,757,781]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Laudonia 
<taxonomicName box="[848,952,757,781]" class="Trilobita" family="Biceratopsidae" genus="Lochmanolenellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Redlichiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bispinata">bispinata</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
was determined to be the immediate sistertaxon to the 
<taxonomicName box="[292,461,793,818]" class="Trilobita" family="Biceratopsidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Redlichiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Biceratopsidae</taxonomicName>
, with 
<taxonomicName box="[531,772,793,817]" class="Trilobita" family="Holmiidae" genus="Mummaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Redlichiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occidens">
<emphasis box="[531,772,793,817]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Mummaspis occidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[828,1092,793,817]" class="Trilobita" family="Laudoniidae" genus="Fritzolenellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Redlichiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truemani">
<emphasis box="[828,1092,793,817]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fritzolenellus truemani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forming successive outgroups to the [
<emphasis box="[244,469,829,853]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Laudonia 
<taxonomicName box="[365,469,829,853]" class="Trilobita" family="Biceratopsidae" genus="Lochmanolenellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Redlichiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bispinata">bispinata</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
+ 
<taxonomicName box="[513,683,829,854]" class="Trilobita" family="Biceratopsidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Redlichiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Biceratopsidae</taxonomicName>
] clade (
<bibRefCitation author="Lieberman" box="[783,986,829,854]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Lieberman, B. S. (1998) Cladistic analysis of the Early Cambrian olenelloid trilobites. Journal of Paleontology, 72, 59 - 78." type="journal article" year="1998">
Lieberman, 
<number box="[926,986,830,854]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). For convenience, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lieberman" box="[1226,1436,829,854]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Lieberman, B. S. (1998) Cladistic analysis of the Early Cambrian olenelloid trilobites. Journal of Paleontology, 72, 59 - 78." type="journal article" year="1998">
Lieberman (
<number box="[1370,1428,830,854]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1998.0">1998</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
grouped 
<emphasis box="[265,372,865,889]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Laudonia</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Fritz, 1992" authorityName="Fritz" authorityYear="1992" box="[402,701,865,890]" class="Trilobita" family="Holmiidae" genus="Mummaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Redlichiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[402,537,866,889]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Mummaspis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fritz" box="[559,701,865,890]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Fritz, W. H. (1992) Walcott's Lower Cambrian olenellid trilobites collection 61 k, Mount Robson area, Canadian Rocky Mountains. Geological Survey of Canada Bulletin, 432, 1 - 65." type="journal article" year="1992">
Fritz, 
<number box="[642,701,866,890]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Lieberman, 1998" authorityName="Lieberman" authorityYear="1998" box="[790,1174,865,890]" class="Trilobita" family="Laudoniidae" genus="Fritzolenellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Redlichiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[790,946,865,889]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fritzolenellus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lieberman" box="[968,1174,865,890]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Lieberman, B. S. (1998) Cladistic analysis of the Early Cambrian olenelloid trilobites. Journal of Paleontology, 72, 59 - 78." type="journal article" year="1998">
Lieberman, 
<number box="[1118,1174,866,890]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
into 
<bibRefCitation author="Lieberman" box="[1263,1275,866,889]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Lieberman, B. S. (1998) Cladistic analysis of the Early Cambrian olenelloid trilobites. Journal of Paleontology, 72, 59 - 78." type="journal article" year="1998" yearSuffix="a">a</bibRefCitation>
paraphyletic “ 
<taxonomicName box="[161,309,901,926]" class="Trilobita" family="Laudoniidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Redlichiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Laudoniidae</taxonomicName>
”. Lieberman’s (
<number box="[497,555,902,926]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1998.0">1998</number>
) cladistic analysis is fraught with problems (e.g., character coding issues discussed following; similar coding problems have been identified in other taxa [
<bibRefCitation author="Webster" box="[1051,1228,937,962]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Webster, M. (2007 a) Ontogeny and evolution of the Early Cambrian trilobite genus Nephrolenellus (Olenelloidea). Journal of Paleontology, 81, 1168 - 1193. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1666 / 06 - 092.1" type="journal article" year="2007" yearSuffix="a">
Webster, 
<number box="[1157,1216,938,962]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2007.0">2007</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Webster" box="[1239,1302,938,962]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Webster, M. (2009) Ontogeny, systematics, and evolution of the effaced early Cambrian trilobites Peachella Walcott, 1910 and Eopeachella new genus (Olenelloidea). Journal of Paleontology, 83, 197 - 218. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1666 / 08 - 106.1" type="journal article" year="2009">
<number box="[1239,1302,938,962]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
]). However, a revised analysis of the phylogenetic affinities of 
<emphasis box="[764,872,973,997]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Laudonia</emphasis>
is beyond the scope of the present paper, and Lieberman’s (
<number box="[306,365,1010,1034]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1998.0">1998</number>
) convention is followed herein.
</paragraph>
